This is my gungame sewer arena map. Yay.
This also happens to be my first map. I picked up hammer for the first time about a week prior to this map's release.
Don't think that's a reason to go light on it though, if you see a problem, tell me about it. It's the only way I'm going to keep getting better.
The arena was designed for gungame, but it works great for a normal Csunter Strike game, Battle Arena, and single weapon games (grenades only/knife fights/etc).
The two teams spawn in opposite rooms, separated by a center chamber. Below the rooms is a sewer system that connects to each of the spawn rooms, and the center chamber. Above, there is a balcony, also connecting the spawn rooms and looks down on the center room.
Enjoy;)

Just download to cstrike\maps
  and enjoy!

This map is currently in beta phase. It is a redo of a map I made previously but I decided to go with dev textures this time as I noticed with all the various sight lines it felt cluttered. Looking for feedback of all kinds, good and bad. This map is large and not suggested for people that are not patient or who are not skilled enough to not fall to their deaths. I like where the map is now, but am looking for feedback as to what might make it more fun. 
Thank you to Komaokc who created the skybox I am using. I try to use custom skyboxes on my dev texture maps and went with this one because of the quality and the similarity in color to my map. 
All comments left on changes will be considered.
IF feedback after a couple weeks is positive I will change this maps status to final.

Edit: 
I edited the map's name since there was a few problems when downloading it to servers. So I made the name shorter. If you had a problem with it before, try again.

This map is a remake from the origonal fy_iceworld map. In mine I took away the guns that are normally at the start and put in buy zones instead. 
I also cut a chunk out of each of the 4 main blocks in the map so you can go through the middle of them and into the middle of the map.
I also added 8 ladders which lead to higher areas of the map (highest is a platform I added). 
I also raised the skybox, added blocks on top of the 4 main blocks and doubled the amount of spawn points from the origonal (origonal had 24, this one has 48). Although 48 people would be crouded for this map, I tested it with 30 bots and it was rather fun.

I remade this map to extend the amount of strategic moves you can make to kill your opponent. 
Although the general idea of this map hasn't changed, I made it so a gun game server could successfully run it with no problems or complications.

The addition of the buy zone was placed so that people would stop complaining when another person took the gun they want. I know personally that every time I play in an iceworld map, there's at least 5 or 6 people that will compain everytime when they don't get their gun. With the buy zone, they don't have to worry about that if the map is being played in a normal gameplay format.

This is the fourth, and final, map in the fy_deagle_x9 series. Enjoy!

I designed this map on graph paper from the start, setting up the boxes in a way that would be fun to play in. Once it was finished I wasn't going to finish the map, I was just going to trash it, but Tr33t (glitch) said he'd take them and finish them. A little ways into the map he suggested that we should make this a group project.

The fy_deagle_x9 project is going to be a set of 4 different deagle maps all specially designed by me. I made the boxes and alligned them properly, then tr33t put in the lighting, the walls, the floor and the roof. I finished it by putting in the bridge over the boxes, adding cubemaps, and putting in spawn points then making the .nav file. 

I hope you enjoy it!

I made this map, it's not a part of the origonal deagle_x9 series, but it's the 5th map in the series that was origonally suppose to be only 4 maps. But I was trying to think of more ideas for the series to expand it so it'll have more than just 4 maps in the series and I thought of having 4 Giant boxes. The "H" in the x9h part stands for Huge to resemble the size of the main 4 boxes. But unlike the first 4, I made this one all on my own. The others I worked on as a project with Glitch (aka Tr33t) and submitted them together with him. 

The map itself holds more players than I planned on putting in, but I could fit more, so I did. It holds upto 42, although I would highly recommend not playing with that many people on a small map like this. 

The lighting turned out very nice, the map looks very dark because of the textures I used, but the lighting makes it look like a bright dark color, so it's like you're playing in a dark map but you can see just fine where you're going.
